{{Infobox glacier | child = | name = Blair Glacier | other_name = | photo = Antarctica Map.png | photo_width = 250px | photo_alt = | photo_caption = Map of Antarctica, with Wilkes Land slightly to the right | map = Antarctica | map_width = | map_alt = | map_caption = Location of Blair Glacier in [[Antarctica]] | mark = Blue_pog.svg | type = | location = [[Wilkes Land]] | coordinates = {{coord|66|45|00|S|124|32|00|E|region:AQ|format=dms|display=inline}} | coords_ref = | area = | length = | width = | thickness = unknown | elevation_max = | elevation_min = | terminus = [[Maury Bay]] | status = unknown | embedded = }}
'''Blair Glacier''' ({{Coord|66|45|S|124|32|E|source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is a [[glacier]] draining northward to the western corner of [[Maury Bay]]. It was delineated from aerial photographs taken by [[U.S. Navy Operation Highjump]] (1946–47), and named by the [[Advisory Committee on Antarctic Names]] for [[James L. Blair]], Midshipman on the sloop [[USS Peacock (1813)|''Peacock'']] during the [[United States Exploring Expedition]] (1838–42) under Lieutenant [[Charles Wilkes]].
