'''Harbi al-Himyari''' ({{lang-ar|'''حربي الحميري'''}} {{transl|ar|'''Ḥarbī al-Ḥimyarī'''}}), was an [[Arab]] [[scholar]] from [[Yemen]], who lived between the 7th and 8th century AD. He is the mentor for teaching [[Koran]] and mathematics to [[Jābir ibn Hayyān]].<ref>[[Eric John Holmyard]], ''Makers of Chemistry''. London: Oxford University Press, 1931</ref> According to Holmyard nothing else is known about him.

