[[File:Drosera filiformis hibernacula Darwiniana.jpg|thumb|A ''[[Drosera filiformis]]'' hibernaculum]] '''Hibernaculum''' (plural ''hibernacula'') is the term often applied to a winter bud of certain [[aquatic plant]]s, such as the [[bladderwort]]s (''[[Bladderwort|Utricularia]]''). The buds are heavier than water, and, being developed at the approach of cold weather, they become detached, sink to the bottom of the pond, and thus survive the winter. In the spring, they enlarge, developing [[buoyancy|air space]]s, rise to the surface, and reproduce their species.<ref>[[New International Encyclopedia]]</ref>
Certain terrestrial plants also form hibernacula. These include some temperate sundews (''[[Drosera]]'') such as ''[[Drosera anglica|D.&nbsp;anglica]]'', ''[[Drosera filiformis|D.&nbsp;filiformis]]'', ''[[Drosera intermedia|D.&nbsp;intermedia]]'', ''[[Drosera rotundifolia|D.&nbsp;rotundifolia]]''; and some temperate butterworts (''[[Pinguicula]]'') such as ''[[Pinguicula balcanica|P.&nbsp;balcanica]]'', ''[[Pinguicula grandiflora|P.&nbsp;grandiflora]]'', ''[[Pinguicula longifolia|P.&nbsp;longifolia]]'', and ''[[Pinguicula vulgaris|P.&nbsp;vulgaris]]''.
==See also== * [[Hibernaculum (disambiguation)|Hibernaculum]] * [[Turion (botany)]]
