'''Kilden – Information Centre for Gender Research''' (''Kilden – informasjonssenter for kjønnsforskning'')<ref>{{cite web|last=|first=|title=Tverrfaglig kjønnsforskning - Fagressurser|url=http://www.ub.uio.no/fag/samfunn-politikk/kjonnsforsk/|publisher=[[University Library of Oslo]]|author=|archivedate=2013-04-27|page=|language=|date=|quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Samenes kvinnekamp viktigere enn innvandrernes|journal=[[Utrop]]|date=2013-04-21|year=|url=http://www.utrop.no/24930}}</ref> is a [[gender research]] center established in 1998 by [[The Research Council of Norway|Research Council of Norway]].
==Organization== The centre is a subdivision of [[The Research Council of Norway|Research Council of Norway]], with a board of directors appointed by the council's [[CEO]]. It reports to the council's Science Division.
